# Warnings, errors, and status badges (Mantine)

For **warnings**, **errors**, and **critical blocking states** (`color="red"` on `Alert` or `Badge`):

- Use **filled** style: omit `variant` on `Alert`, or set `variant="filled"`.
- On `Badge`, use `variant="filled"`.
- Do **not** use `color="yellow"`, `orange`, or `amber` for warnings or unavailable/critical states – use **red**.
- Do **not** use `variant="light"` for these – it looks muddy in dark mode and is too weak.

**Success** status (`color="green"` on Alert or Badge): use `variant="filled"`, not `variant="light"`.

Neutral/info alerts (`gray`, `blue`) may use `variant="light"` when a subtle tone is intended.

`Button` and `ThemeIcon` are not covered here; `variant="light"` on those is still fine when appropriate.

```tsx
// Good – warning / error / blocked Alert
<Alert color="red" variant="filled" title="Import not available">...</Alert>

// Good – status Badge
<Badge color="green" variant="filled">Succeeded</Badge>
<Badge color={minioOk ? 'green' : 'red'} variant="filled">MinIO OK</Badge>

// Avoid
<Alert color="yellow" variant="filled" title="...">...</Alert>
<Alert color="yellow" variant="light" title="...">...</Alert>
<Badge color="green" variant="light">Succeeded</Badge>
```
